b"[![](../../cdshop/cdinfo.jpg)](../../cdshop/index.htm)  \n[Sacred Texts](../../index.htm)  [Hinduism](../index.htm)  [Index](index.htm)\n[Previous](sbe29047.htm)  [Next](sbe29049.htm)\n\n* * *\n\n[Buy this Book at\nAmazon.com](http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/1421228750/internetsacredte)\n\n* * *\n\n_The Grihya Sutras, Part 1 (SBE29)_ , by Hermann Oldenberg, [1886], at sacred-\ntexts.com\n\n* * *\n\n### KHA _N_ _D_ A 18.\n\n1\\. A student who is going to set out on a journey, speaks thus to his\nteacher:\n\n2 2. 'Of inhalation and exhalation'\xc2\x97(this he says) in a low voice; 'Om, I will\ndwell'\xc2\x97this aloud.\n\n3\\. (The teacher) in a low voice (replies), 'To inhalation and exhalation I,\nthe wide-extended one, resort with thee. To the protecting god I give thee in\ncharge. God Savitar; this student belongs to thee; I give him in charge to\nthee; protect him; do not forsake him.'\n\n4\\. 'Om, hail!' the teacher aloud. 'Hail!' the teacher aloud.\n\nHere ends the Second Adhyaya.\n\n* * *\n\n### Footnotes\n\n[90:2](sbe29048.htm#fr_201) 18, 2. Perhaps vatsyami (I will dwell) is a sort\nof euphemism for pravatsyami (I will go away).\n\n* * *\n\n[Next: III, 1](sbe29049.htm)\n\n"